article.headline: Askew scores 28 as Long Beach State beats Hawaii 76-68
article.description: — Devin Askew had 28 points in Long Beach State's 76-68 victory over Hawaii on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Askew scores 28 as Long Beach State beats Hawaii 76-68
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- — Devin Askew had 28 points in Long Beach State's 76-68 victory over Hawaii on Saturday night. Askew also had six rebounds, seven assists, and seven steals for the Beach (3-8, 2-0 Big West Conference). Austin Johnson scored 14 points and added 10 rebounds. TJ Wainwright went 5 of 9 from the field (2 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 14 points. The Rainbow Warriors (5-3, 0-1) were led in scoring by Marcus Greene, who finished with 17 points. Gytis Nemeiksa added 14 points, seven rebounds and two steals for Hawaii. Akira Jacobs also had 11 points. Long Beach State takes on San Diego on the road on Tuesday, and Hawaii hosts Texas A&M-CC on Sunday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
